        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:21PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from East Point to Snapfinger to near Snellville, and
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Conyers, East Point, Forest Park, Snellville, Riverdale,
College Park, Loganville, Morrow, Hapeville, Lake City, Lithonia,
Hartsfield-Jackson Airport, Lakeview Estates, Rex, Belmont, Arabia
Mountain, Big Haynes Creek Park, Rosebud, and Hidden Valley Park.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
